GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU 5

00:36:21.618 --> 00:36:24.162
As this is said to be
the final season of Kang Pil-gu,

00:36:24.246 --> 00:36:25.706
the viewers are deeply disappointed.

00:36:25.789 --> 00:36:27.165
Is it truly over?

00:36:28.166 --> 00:36:29.292
Yes.

00:36:29.376 --> 00:36:30.585
That's the case for now.

00:36:31.169 --> 00:36:33.755
It can't continue
just because I want it to.

00:36:35.007 --> 00:36:35.841
But…

00:36:36.758 --> 00:36:38.885
if there's a chance down the road,

00:36:39.970 --> 00:36:42.264
I'd love to meet Kang Pil-gu again.

00:36:46.184 --> 00:36:47.060
Wow.

00:36:49.021 --> 00:36:50.480
Deep down,

00:36:51.773 --> 00:36:52.733
I already miss him.

00:36:54.985 --> 00:36:57.446
Well, Mr. Lim Hyeon-jun.

00:36:57.529 --> 00:37:00.157
Is there anyone else that you miss
or would like to see right now?

00:37:01.867 --> 00:37:02.701
Yes.

00:37:06.329 --> 00:37:07.247
There is.

00:38:07.265 --> 00:38:09.810
AT NUNGNAE STATION

00:38:12.104 --> 00:38:13.814
A PLACE WHERE LONGING GATHERS LIKE SNOW

00:38:16.066 --> 00:38:18.110
AND TENDER GREETINGS GATHER
LIKE AUTUMN LEAVES

00:38:32.541 --> 00:38:35.585
If you'd like, I can share
a simple feel-good method.

00:38:36.378 --> 00:38:39.798
Go outside on a sunny day
and simply stand there.

00:38:39.881 --> 00:38:40.966
That's it?

00:38:41.550 --> 00:38:43.260
After standing for a while,

00:38:43.343 --> 00:38:45.720
your head will start to feel warm
from the sunshine.

00:38:46.221 --> 00:38:48.098
When that happens,

00:38:48.682 --> 00:38:50.642
it feels like someone
is gently stroking your head.

00:38:58.358 --> 00:38:59.317
It feels warm.

00:39:13.456 --> 00:39:14.583
Kang Pil-gu is

00:39:14.666 --> 00:39:18.295
really, really special.

00:39:19.296 --> 00:39:22.132
And you got to play
that extraordinary Kang Pil-gu.

00:39:23.049 --> 00:39:24.259
How lucky is that?

00:39:37.230 --> 00:39:38.815
Wow, what's this?

00:39:39.399 --> 00:39:40.859
-What's all this?
-Goodness.

00:39:40.942 --> 00:39:42.360
-You're back already?
-Yes.

00:39:42.444 --> 00:39:44.571
I was going to leave
right after making dinner,

00:39:44.654 --> 00:39:46.781
but I forgot to make you soup.

00:39:46.865 --> 00:39:47.949
What kind of soup?

00:39:48.033 --> 00:39:49.534
Oh, seaweed soup.

00:39:50.118 --> 00:39:51.203
That sounds delicious.

00:39:51.286 --> 00:39:52.996
Sit down. Let's eat together.

00:39:54.122 --> 00:39:55.832
-Together?
-Yes.

00:40:02.088 --> 00:40:05.175
So, is that nice lady reporter

00:40:05.258 --> 00:40:06.509
still not back from Seria yet?

00:40:08.261 --> 00:40:09.512
How do you know her?

00:40:10.639 --> 00:40:11.640
Oh, well…

00:40:11.723 --> 00:40:13.892
I came by once

00:40:13.975 --> 00:40:17.145
and found her here
while she was recovering from the flu.

00:40:17.229 --> 00:40:18.063
I see.

00:40:19.564 --> 00:40:21.942
Mom, you didn't
say anything weird, did you?

00:40:23.276 --> 00:40:24.527
Of course I didn't.

00:40:27.322 --> 00:40:28.865
When she gets back,

00:40:28.949 --> 00:40:30.742
could you introduce me to her?

00:40:36.456 --> 00:40:37.290
Okay.

00:40:37.374 --> 00:40:38.416
Really?

00:40:38.500 --> 00:40:39.793
Yeah.

00:40:41.461 --> 00:40:42.337
I'll bring the soup.

00:40:52.764 --> 00:40:55.058
Can you please stop nagging me?

00:40:55.558 --> 00:40:57.644
I told you I couldn't call
because I lost my phone.

00:40:57.727 --> 00:40:59.813
Are you sure you're not lying?

00:40:59.896 --> 00:41:01.147
I'm not lying.

00:41:01.231 --> 00:41:03.525
I had a hard time
borrowing this phone to call you.

00:41:03.608 --> 00:41:05.151
Are you badly hurt?

00:41:05.235 --> 00:41:08.571
I was told your injury was pretty severe.

00:41:08.655 --> 00:41:09.489
I'm fine.

00:41:09.572 --> 00:41:10.949
Get better and come home.

00:41:11.533 --> 00:41:13.660
Is there anything you want to eat
when you return?

00:41:14.703 --> 00:41:15.829
It'll be my treat.

00:41:30.552 --> 00:41:32.721
REPORTER WI JEONG-SIN

00:41:34.973 --> 00:41:37.225
Gosh, she's heartless.

00:41:37.726 --> 00:41:39.811
She hasn't texted me once.

00:41:52.824 --> 00:41:54.326
WI JEONG-SIN

00:42:18.808 --> 00:42:19.642
She's so cute.

00:42:24.773 --> 00:42:26.066
You were adorable.

00:42:37.827 --> 00:42:38.703
My phone!

00:42:44.501 --> 00:42:46.044
Oh, man.

00:42:50.256 --> 00:42:51.341
It's on.

00:42:51.424 --> 00:42:52.342
It's working.

00:43:02.852 --> 00:43:03.686
It's working.

00:43:09.109 --> 00:43:09.943
LIM HYEON-JUN

00:43:10.026 --> 00:43:11.611
HOW ARE YOU? THE WEATHER IS NICE HERE.
COME BACK SOON.

00:43:11.694 --> 00:43:13.279
I WENT TO THE HANGANG RIVER TODAY.
I MISS YOU.

00:43:25.125 --> 00:43:27.085
EVERYTHING'S OKAY, RIGHT?
I'LL TELL MYSELF THAT NO NEWS IS GOOD NEWS

00:43:40.765 --> 00:43:41.599
ONION

00:43:46.563 --> 00:43:48.356
MELOMASTER
A LONELY SINGLE KANG PIL-GU SOCK

00:43:56.030 --> 00:44:00.452
I found a single Kang Pil-gu sock
all by itself in Hannam-dong.

00:44:00.535 --> 00:44:02.287
It's being kept safe at the moment.

00:44:02.370 --> 00:44:05.373
If you have lost it,
please contact me promptly

00:44:05.457 --> 00:44:08.168
and rescue this Pil-gu sock
from loneliness.

00:44:08.251 --> 00:44:10.753
I can be reached anytime.

00:44:10.837 --> 00:44:11.754
However,

00:44:11.838 --> 00:44:13.965
transactions are strictly in person.

00:44:14.048 --> 00:44:15.383
PRICE: 1,000,000 WON

00:44:22.515 --> 00:44:24.142
This is hilarious.

00:44:28.062 --> 00:44:28.938
It's too much.

00:44:58.676 --> 00:44:59.511
Huh?

00:45:01.387 --> 00:45:02.263
Hey, Seon-u!

00:45:03.723 --> 00:45:05.058
Seon-u!

00:45:05.141 --> 00:45:06.518
Yeah? What is it?

00:45:06.601 --> 00:45:08.228
-Get over here.
-What's going on?

00:45:08.311 --> 00:45:09.729
This right here.

00:45:10.271 --> 00:45:13.024
This is an email
inviting me to their audition, right?

00:45:14.859 --> 00:45:16.277
YOU ARE ONE OF THE
FINAL CANDIDATES FOR THIS ROLE.

00:45:16.361 --> 00:45:17.820
OUR PRODUCER, MARK JONES,
WILL BE VISITING SEOUL.

00:45:17.904 --> 00:45:18.780
Right?

00:45:18.863 --> 00:45:20.240
Yeah, you're right.

00:45:21.324 --> 00:45:23.451
It's not just an audition.
You're a final candidate.

00:45:25.578 --> 00:45:27.622
Hyeon-jun, they're coming to see you!

00:45:33.586 --> 00:45:36.589
"For the role of Kevin Kim."

00:45:37.590 --> 00:45:38.925
So my name will be Kevin Kim?

00:45:39.008 --> 00:45:40.093
Onion!

00:45:50.061 --> 00:45:52.397
Do you still have the single sock?

00:45:57.652 --> 00:45:58.778
Yes, I still have it.

00:46:01.781 --> 00:46:03.074
I think that sock's mine.

00:46:03.157 --> 00:46:06.661
I think that Kang Pil-gu sock
belongs to me.

00:46:07.870 --> 00:46:10.957
You need to bring
the other sock to verify it.

00:46:11.040 --> 00:46:12.000
Okay.

00:46:12.083 --> 00:46:13.042
I'll bring it.

00:46:18.381 --> 00:46:20.008
When can we make the transaction?

00:46:20.091 --> 00:46:21.968
The poorsock is so lonely,

00:46:22.051 --> 00:46:24.262
it's on the verge of depression.

00:46:25.346 --> 00:46:27.015
Oh, dear.

00:46:27.098 --> 00:46:29.183
I'm overseas at the moment.

00:46:30.226 --> 00:46:31.728
How about next month on the 23rd?

00:46:31.811 --> 00:46:32.979
The 23rd?

00:46:39.152 --> 00:46:40.111
The 23rd.

00:46:41.279 --> 00:46:43.323
You're making me wait too long.

00:46:43.823 --> 00:46:45.033
If this deal falls through,

00:46:45.116 --> 00:46:47.493
I'm sure the other buyers
will be thrilled.

00:46:47.577 --> 00:46:48.661
No, wait!

00:46:48.745 --> 00:46:50.622
I promise I'll buy it.

00:46:53.499 --> 00:46:54.751
SCHEDULE A TRANSACTION

00:46:56.502 --> 00:46:57.503
AN APPOINTMENT HAS BEEN BOOKED

00:46:57.587 --> 00:47:00.214
Where would you like to meet
for the transaction?

00:47:01.341 --> 00:47:02.508
How about the N Seoul Tower?

00:47:02.592 --> 00:47:03.926
That sounds good.

00:47:06.179 --> 00:47:08.973
I actually had a bad experience
at N Seoul Tower once.

00:47:09.057 --> 00:47:11.309
But I want to put it behind me now.

00:47:11.392 --> 00:47:14.145
Then meet me on the 23rd at 8 p.m.,

00:47:14.228 --> 00:47:16.356
by the love locks at the N Seoul Tower.

00:47:16.856 --> 00:47:20.234
You won't send
someone else in your place, will you?

00:47:20.735 --> 00:47:22.779
If you're curious, hurry up and come.

00:48:45.820 --> 00:48:46.738
Let me look at you.

00:48:48.614 --> 00:48:49.449
You didn't get hurt?

00:48:50.074 --> 00:48:51.033
I missed you.

00:48:54.912 --> 00:48:56.247
Didn't you miss me?

00:48:57.498 --> 00:48:59.167
Of course, I missed you!

00:48:59.917 --> 00:49:03.171
Jeez, how could you not text me once?

00:49:04.172 --> 00:49:07.383
I lost my phone, and something came up.

00:49:08.885 --> 00:49:09.761
I'm sorry.

00:49:12.472 --> 00:49:14.807
It's okay. I understand.

00:49:16.559 --> 00:49:19.020
I've been doing pretty well.

00:49:19.604 --> 00:49:21.689
Things aren't as bad for me as I expected.

00:49:22.231 --> 00:49:25.318
A lot of people told me
that I did what Kang Pil-gu would've done.

00:49:26.402 --> 00:49:27.779
I knew it.

00:49:27.862 --> 00:49:29.113
It's the truth, after all.

00:49:49.592 --> 00:49:51.219
Wait, is it okay for us to be like this?

00:49:52.053 --> 00:49:53.721
Stop worrying about what others think.

00:49:53.805 --> 00:49:55.431
Who cares what they think?

00:50:10.279 --> 00:50:14.116
HYEON-JUN & JEONG-SIN

00:50:37.723 --> 00:50:38.766
Will you be leaving again?

00:50:40.810 --> 00:50:42.812
Why? Are you afraid I might?

00:50:42.895 --> 00:50:43.813
Hey.

00:50:44.814 --> 00:50:47.650
I won't let go of your hand
if you go somewhere dangerous again.

00:50:49.026 --> 00:50:49.861
Where should I go?

00:50:49.944 --> 00:50:50.778
What?

00:50:52.113 --> 00:50:52.947
So you'll leave again?

00:50:54.156 --> 00:50:55.533
I'm not going anywhere.

00:50:56.242 --> 00:50:57.243
Are you sure?

00:50:58.119 --> 00:50:59.871
-Fine, I'll go then.
-Hey.

00:51:04.500 --> 00:51:05.877
Home sweet home.

00:51:06.502 --> 00:51:07.670
There's no place like home.

00:51:21.100 --> 00:51:24.478
GWON SE-NA ANNOUNCES RETIREMENT
AND LEAVES FOR A FASHION SCHOOL IN THE US

00:51:37.575 --> 00:51:39.911
Wow, is this for real?

00:51:39.994 --> 00:51:42.580
I can't believe
you're going to be in a Hollywood movie.

00:51:43.539 --> 00:51:45.958
All of our effort has finally paid off.

00:51:46.751 --> 00:51:47.793
I know, right?

00:51:47.877 --> 00:51:52.298
Back when we recorded your audition tape
and you were doing lines from Goblin,

00:51:52.381 --> 00:51:54.675
I wondered what the hell we were doing.

00:51:54.759 --> 00:51:57.678
Who would've thought
a day like this would come?

00:51:58.429 --> 00:52:02.141
They say the road less traveled
is never easy.

00:52:03.893 --> 00:52:06.938
By the way, Mr. Hwang.
Why have you been so busy lately?

00:52:07.021 --> 00:52:08.272
I never see you around.

00:52:09.065 --> 00:52:11.817
He's been really busy because of Hong-sin.

00:52:11.901 --> 00:52:13.194
"But I do!"

00:52:13.277 --> 00:52:15.947
Very nice.
Raise the handcuffs a bit higher.

00:52:16.030 --> 00:52:18.199
Let's go for a more intense gaze
and a different pose.

00:52:19.158 --> 00:52:21.285
-That's great.
-Good Detective Kang Pil-gu!

00:52:21.369 --> 00:52:22.453
Right, King's Back does need

00:52:22.536 --> 00:52:25.665
a new actor to follow in the footsteps
of Lim Hyeon-jun.

00:52:27.124 --> 00:52:29.168
Speaking of which, Seon-u…

00:52:29.752 --> 00:52:32.713
He's holding up as an intern right now.
He won't turn to acting again, will he?

00:52:32.797 --> 00:52:34.882
Of course not!

00:52:34.966 --> 00:52:38.219
He's too busy with his internship
at the hospital.

00:52:38.302 --> 00:52:40.262
Please save him!

00:52:40.346 --> 00:52:42.390
Secure his airway
and get ready to intubate him.

00:52:42.473 --> 00:52:43.891
The intubation kit is ready.

00:52:43.975 --> 00:52:45.685
I have to say, he's really smart.

00:52:45.768 --> 00:52:48.854
He realized his path early on
and went for it.

00:52:49.855 --> 00:52:52.024
He's smart because he takes after me.

00:52:53.025 --> 00:52:54.527
By the way, I saw you reading a script.

00:52:54.610 --> 00:52:55.653
Was it for me?

00:52:57.738 --> 00:52:59.115
The thing is,

00:52:59.198 --> 00:53:02.910
we did get a streaming series script, but…

00:53:04.578 --> 00:53:07.498
Gosh, how do I explain this?

00:53:09.041 --> 00:53:10.042
It's just that…

00:53:11.293 --> 00:53:12.837
-Let's see it.
-Yeah.

00:53:12.920 --> 00:53:14.922
It's titled Double Investigation.

00:53:15.006 --> 00:53:17.550
And it's another detective series, I know.

00:53:18.217 --> 00:53:20.386
I read it too
and thought it was really good.

00:53:20.469 --> 00:53:21.762
It's really good.

00:53:23.222 --> 00:53:24.223
So a detective?

00:53:24.306 --> 00:53:25.641
Me, as a detective?

00:53:25.725 --> 00:53:28.811
Yes, you'd play a detective,
but it's a really good…

00:53:28.894 --> 00:53:30.146
-It's good.
-It is.

00:53:30.229 --> 00:53:31.188
Like, totally.

00:53:31.272 --> 00:53:32.523
It's totally good.

00:53:33.691 --> 00:53:35.317
It's total…

00:53:35.401 --> 00:53:38.904
These TV station guys are total jerks!

00:53:38.988 --> 00:53:40.990
He was great as Kang Pil-gu,
but they can't keep giving him

00:53:41.073 --> 00:53:43.451
-the same old detective roles!
-Right.

00:53:43.534 --> 00:53:45.119
We should just tear this script apart.

00:53:45.202 --> 00:53:46.996
No, let me see it.

00:53:47.079 --> 00:53:48.789
No, I'm so offended right now.

00:53:48.873 --> 00:53:51.000
I mean, it is a really good story!

00:53:51.083 --> 00:53:52.418
But we need to tear it up!

00:53:52.501 --> 00:53:55.504
-Fine, I heard you. Give it to me.
-Why?

00:53:55.588 --> 00:53:57.423
Not all detectives are the same.

00:53:58.299 --> 00:53:59.633
I'm a different kind of detective.

00:54:00.259 --> 00:54:01.260
I'll give it a read.

00:54:03.262 --> 00:54:06.557
Bro, you've totally changed.

00:54:06.640 --> 00:54:08.601
Hey, should I ask Mr. Bak

00:54:08.684 --> 00:54:10.811
to write a new season of Kang Pil-gu?

00:54:12.188 --> 00:54:13.898
I think he's busy writing something else.

00:54:13.981 --> 00:54:17.276
"Like a scene from a painting,

00:54:17.359 --> 00:54:20.112
their silhouettes
fade into the city lights…"

00:54:21.113 --> 00:54:22.323
THE END

00:54:22.406 --> 00:54:24.075
NICE TO NOT MEET YOU
SCRIPT

00:54:24.158 --> 00:54:26.952
"A connection destined by fate,
born from a rice cooker transaction."

00:54:27.703 --> 00:54:29.163
What kind of nonsense is this?

00:54:29.246 --> 00:54:30.790
Come on, Mr. Son.

00:54:30.873 --> 00:54:32.833
The buzzword these days is "harmlessness."

00:54:32.917 --> 00:54:34.502
I've moved on from crime stories

00:54:34.585 --> 00:54:36.921
to ones that are
lighthearted and harmless.

00:54:37.004 --> 00:54:40.049
It only makes sense
that a script that's written by you

00:54:40.132 --> 00:54:44.428
has cars flipping left and right
and metal pipes flying everywhere.

00:54:44.512 --> 00:54:46.097
But "Nice to Not Meet You"?

00:54:46.639 --> 00:54:48.599
Jeez, even the title is tacky.

00:54:49.517 --> 00:54:50.559
It's retro.

00:54:51.268 --> 00:54:52.770
And what about the cast?

00:54:52.853 --> 00:54:55.648
Who'd want to be in a rom-com
written by the writer of Kang Pil-gu?

00:54:55.731 --> 00:54:56.565
Kang Pil-gu himself?

00:54:57.858 --> 00:54:59.276
That's not a bad idea.

00:55:11.372 --> 00:55:12.623
Be careful when you're running.

00:55:12.706 --> 00:55:13.541
Okay.

00:55:16.585 --> 00:55:17.419
Here.

00:55:19.880 --> 00:55:21.507
FAMILY RELATIONSHIP CERTIFICATE

00:55:21.590 --> 00:55:22.758
WIFE: YUN HWA-YEONG, CHILD: LEE JAE-HA

00:55:26.428 --> 00:55:28.055
It looks like
Yun Jae-ha is now Lee Jae-ha.

00:55:31.016 --> 00:55:32.226
It makes me a little sad.

00:55:33.727 --> 00:55:34.770
It's like you've stolen my son.

00:55:37.106 --> 00:55:38.440
He's my son, too, you know.

00:55:42.903 --> 00:55:44.363
Don't be so sad.

00:55:44.989 --> 00:55:46.907
You got yourself
an amazing husband in return.

00:55:48.909 --> 00:55:49.910
You're right.

00:55:55.040 --> 00:55:56.417
-Jae-ha.
-Yes?

00:55:57.334 --> 00:55:58.460
-Are you having fun?
-Yes.

00:56:02.131 --> 00:56:03.465
Here, I'll do it for you.

00:56:13.350 --> 00:56:14.727
Hey, Su-ji. Are you sleeping?

00:56:14.810 --> 00:56:15.728
Of course not.

00:56:15.811 --> 00:56:18.689
I'm awake at all times for you, Mr. Lim.

00:56:24.653 --> 00:56:27.239
There's a woman I'd like to propose to.

00:56:27.323 --> 00:56:28.407
Who's this skank?

00:56:31.452 --> 00:56:32.745
-What?
-I'm just kidding.

00:56:32.828 --> 00:56:34.371
Please continue.

00:56:37.666 --> 00:56:39.627
There's a woman I really like.

00:56:40.252 --> 00:56:42.338
What would be
the best way to propose to her?

00:56:46.884 --> 00:56:47.968
Su-ji?

00:56:48.928 --> 00:56:50.846
-Su-ji?
-I didn't quite get that.

00:56:50.930 --> 00:56:52.097
Hey, Su-ji!

00:56:52.181 --> 00:56:53.390
What's wrong with her?

00:56:58.229 --> 00:57:00.231
Why are you suddenly playing trot music?

00:57:02.233 --> 00:57:03.150
Hey, Su-ji!

00:57:03.984 --> 00:57:04.860
Su-ji…

00:57:12.993 --> 00:57:15.871
"ASK ME ANYTHING"

00:57:17.873 --> 00:57:19.124
Give me a dramatic

00:57:19.667 --> 00:57:23.170
and fail-proof idea to propose to someone.

00:57:24.213 --> 00:57:26.715
The key element is sincerity.

00:57:26.799 --> 00:57:29.468
How about expressing your feelings

00:57:29.551 --> 00:57:31.303
in a place where they felt most genuine?

00:57:31.387 --> 00:57:32.221
If you would like,

00:57:32.304 --> 00:57:34.932
I can give you step-by-step instructions.

00:57:37.476 --> 00:57:38.394
Wow.

00:57:39.353 --> 00:57:40.896
You understand me right away.

00:57:41.730 --> 00:57:44.608
All right,
walk me through it step by step.

00:58:10.426 --> 00:58:11.844
Did you see the article this morning?

00:58:13.053 --> 00:58:14.763
Well, it was bound to happen.

00:58:16.348 --> 00:58:19.101
The chief called me and gave me an earful.

00:58:19.184 --> 00:58:20.394
Hey, Wi Jeong-sin.

00:58:20.477 --> 00:58:21.478
Have you lost your mind?

00:58:21.562 --> 00:58:23.814
How could you let another outlet
publish this exclusive?

00:58:23.897 --> 00:58:26.984
Come on, don't let it bother you.

00:58:27.067 --> 00:58:28.152
Don't worry about it.

00:58:29.361 --> 00:58:30.821
I dreamed of coming back to Korea

00:58:30.904 --> 00:58:34.825
and sitting on a park bench like this,
basking in the sun as much as I wanted.

00:58:35.701 --> 00:58:36.744
I love it.

00:58:37.619 --> 00:58:38.537
And I'm right here, next to you.

00:58:39.496 --> 00:58:40.331
Right in front of me, too.

00:58:46.003 --> 00:58:47.838
I thought it'd be a huge deal

00:58:47.921 --> 00:58:50.716
if an ordinary person like me
dated an actor.

00:58:51.342 --> 00:58:53.427
-But it really isn't.
-Of course, it's not.

00:58:54.720 --> 00:58:56.930
Why was I so intimidated
by the idea back then?

00:58:57.848 --> 00:58:58.891
Somebody once said

00:58:58.974 --> 00:59:01.268
that it's the simple,
everyday life that saves us.

00:59:03.604 --> 00:59:07.024
Life is easiest
when it's simple and calm like this.

00:59:08.067 --> 00:59:09.526
What else is there in life?

00:59:09.610 --> 00:59:11.445
The greatest happiness
is just being comfortable.

00:59:12.488 --> 00:59:13.655
Wow, that's lame.

00:59:16.909 --> 00:59:17.910
Shall we walk?

00:59:31.799 --> 00:59:33.550
Catch me if you can!

00:59:40.307 --> 00:59:42.351
SEONGIL STATION

00:59:44.770 --> 00:59:46.563
Jeez, what's taking them so long?

00:59:50.317 --> 00:59:51.777
I'm sure they'll find me on their own.

00:59:51.860 --> 00:59:53.320
Wow, it's that scene now.

00:59:53.404 --> 00:59:54.863
-Onion!
-"Onion"?

00:59:57.991 --> 00:59:58.867
Onion?

01:00:13.298 --> 01:00:14.299
You're here from Onion, right?

01:00:14.383 --> 01:00:15.467
What?

01:00:15.551 --> 01:00:17.511
Oh, that's right. Onion.

01:00:17.594 --> 01:00:18.470
Is this it?

01:00:20.597 --> 01:00:22.474
I just sent you 320,000 won
through Onion Pay.

01:00:23.434 --> 01:00:24.476
Excuse me?

01:00:24.560 --> 01:00:26.019
How was I supposed to know what that is?

01:00:28.480 --> 01:00:29.815
I'm a fan of Seo U-jin.

01:00:30.858 --> 01:00:32.192
-Thank you.
-All right, then.

01:00:33.569 --> 01:00:34.403
Excuse me.

01:00:39.324 --> 01:00:41.452
Do you like Seo U-jin?

01:00:43.745 --> 01:00:44.997
Do you like…

01:00:46.582 --> 01:00:47.416
Lim Hyeon-jun?

01:00:47.499 --> 01:00:48.876
Yes, I do.

01:00:51.378 --> 01:00:52.921
It's the first time in my life.

01:00:54.006 --> 01:00:56.300
I've never liked someone
so unconditionally.

01:01:00.554 --> 01:01:02.389
Why did you tell him about this part?

01:01:02.473 --> 01:01:03.682
-Why not?
-I can't…

01:01:03.765 --> 01:01:04.892
Could you keep it down?

01:01:04.975 --> 01:01:05.809
-I'm sorry.
-Sorry.

01:01:09.062 --> 01:01:10.564
Hey, it's Lim Hyeon-jun.

01:01:10.647 --> 01:01:12.274
-Really?
-It's Lim Hyeon-jun.

01:01:12.357 --> 01:01:14.359
It's Lim Hyeon-jun!

